name: cult.ure 04 - Corporation Cult
description:
I recently discovered that my Canadian government travelled to Washington D.C to register itself as a corporation; the Canada Corporation. There are currently more than 20 countries listed as corporations on the Securities Exchange Commission. All of those countries registered in the United States, which itself is a corporation. America and the United States Corporation are two different entities.

What difference does any of this make?  When a corporation owns land it obtains an allodial title for not only that land but everything on it. All infrastructure, all buildings, all animals, all people. The allodial title supersedes all other titles.

The 2016 movie about the founding of Mcdonalds, "The Founder" summed it up perfectly: "...you're not in the burger business sir, you're in the real-estate business."

The human farm with its brilliant shepherds.
